ZH: 这个城市常常有过客来往。
EN: This city often has transient visitors.
ZH: 他在这里只是个过客，不会停留很久。
EN: He is just a passerby here and won't stay for long.
ZH: 他是一个没有归属感的过客。
EN: He is a transient with no sense of belonging.
ZH: 这本书描述了无数过客的故事。
EN: This book depicts the stories of countless passersby.
ZH: 过客经过时，我用眼神和他打了个招呼。
EN: I greeted the passerby with a glance as they walked past.
ZH: 这家咖啡店每天都有来自世界各地的过客。
EN: This coffee shop attracts tourists from all over the world every day.
ZH: 过客们在茶楼前经过，欣赏着美丽的风景。
EN: The passersby walked past the teahouse, enjoying the beautiful scenery.
ZH: 过客匆匆忙忙，转瞬即逝。
EN: Passersby hurriedly come and go, disappearing in a blink of an eye.
ZH: 这位艺术家常常把过客作为自己的创作对象。
EN: This artist often uses passersby as subjects for his artworks.
ZH: 将我仅有的希望寄托给过客。
EN: I put my only hope in the passing stranger.
ZH: 过客们赞叹着这座城市的繁荣。
EN: The passersby marveled at the prosperity of the city.
ZH: 这些街头艺人用音乐吸引着过客。
EN: These street performers attract passersby with their music.
ZH: 我喜欢坐在公园的长椅上，看过客们忙碌的身影。
EN: I enjoy sitting on a park bench, watching the busy figures of passersby.
ZH: 碰到过客，我们可以互换旅行经验。
EN: When we come across a transient, we can exchange travel experiences.
